♪ These happy days ♪

01:07.020 --> 01:09.100
♪ Are yours and mine ♪

01:09.100 --> 01:11.100
♪ These happy days are yours ♪

01:11.100 --> 01:13.020
♪ And mine <i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">, Happy Days{\r}! ♪</font></font></i>

01:17.490 --> 01:19.000
♪ I'm walkin', yes, indeed ♪

01:19.000 --> 01:20.000
♪ I'm talkin' ♪

01:20.000 --> 01:22.000
Happy Days <i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">is filmed
before a studio audience{\r}.</font></font></i>

01:22.420 --> 01:25.000
♪ That you'll come back to me ♪

01:25.000 --> 01:26.500
♪ I'm lonely... ♪

01:26.500 --> 01:29.010
Why do you let me walk
backwards all the time?

01:29.510 --> 01:32.010
Okay, put it on the
table here, Tony.

01:32.010 --> 01:33.960
Okay. Set it down
nice and easy.

01:33.960 --> 01:37.510
Oh, good. Excuse me.

01:37.510 --> 01:39.520
Lift up my side.

01:42.520 --> 01:45.020
That's pain.

01:45.020 --> 01:46.360
Plug it in now,
would you?

01:46.610 --> 01:47.690
Girls, girls...

01:47.690 --> 01:51.190
♪ I'm hopin' that you'll
come back to me ♪

01:51.190 --> 01:54.200
Girls, time out here,
girls, time out here.

01:54.200 --> 01:55.700
Will you
just calm down?

01:56.200 --> 01:57.700
All right, now,
Doris, come here.

01:57.700 --> 01:59.700
You are a terrific driver.
You dig it? Terrific.

01:59.700 --> 02:02.710
Next time, just keep
your hands on the wheel.

02:02.710 --> 02:05.210
That ain't too much
to ask, you know?

02:05.210 --> 02:06.710
Hey, all right.

02:06.710 --> 02:08.710
Excuse me, Fonzie.
I need your advice.

02:08.710 --> 02:09.710
Yeah?

02:09.710 --> 02:11.630
Do you think the TV
set there is okay?

02:11.920 --> 02:14.000
Al, I got other
problems on my mind.

02:14.000 --> 02:15.840
My bike is busted--
can you dig it?

02:16.090 --> 02:18.670
I mean, I got 50 chicks here
dying to drive me home.

02:18.670 --> 02:20.170
Well, what we're
going to do

02:20.170 --> 02:22.180
is we're going
to have all the
football games now

02:22.180 --> 02:24.010
and in color.
Whoopee, Al.

02:24.260 --> 02:25.850
Yeah, well, it's going
to be a big thing,

02:25.850 --> 02:27.850
I mean, since Ralph
started gambling

02:27.850 --> 02:29.150
with those
football cards.

02:29.320 --> 02:30.400
Yeah, I'll
tell you something.

02:30.400 --> 02:31.900
That bubblegum king
is getting out of hand, huh?

02:32.270 --> 02:34.190
What do you think
of the new Ralph?

02:34.440 --> 02:37.020
I think I like
the old one better.

02:37.020 --> 02:39.030
All right, all right,
all right.

02:39.030 --> 02:40.030
Now, girls... girls,
when I get back,

02:40.030 --> 02:41.030
I'm going to
have the answer

02:41.030 --> 02:43.030
to who can drive
me home, all right?

02:43.030 --> 02:44.450
So just...
just keep calm.

02:44.750 --> 02:46.330
Have your driver's license
ready.

02:46.330 --> 02:48.840
No learner's permits.

02:48.840 --> 02:50.340
This is private, girls.

02:57.040 --> 02:59.550
All right, all right,
step right up!

02:59.550 --> 03:01.050
The big game is about to start.

03:01.050 --> 03:02.550
Put your bets down.

03:02.550 --> 03:04.050
College or pro.

03:04.050 --> 03:06.390
All you need
is three teams to win.

03:06.690 --> 03:09.060
Taking candy from a baby,
right, doll face?

03:09.310 --> 03:10.890
Right, sugar lips.

03:10.890 --> 03:13.890
Sugar lips. Thank you.

03:13.890 --> 03:15.860
Okay, check off
your three teams.

03:16.230 --> 03:17.810
Malph, get your
hockey stuff together.

03:17.810 --> 03:19.820
Game starts in 30 minutes.

03:19.820 --> 03:21.820
Sheila, I don't believe
you've met the boys.

03:21.820 --> 03:23.120
Richie and Potsie,

03:23.370 --> 03:25.910
my very close friend Sheila.
Charmed.

03:26.290 --> 03:27.370
Nice to meet you.

03:27.870 --> 03:29.210
Hey, Ralph, come on.
You got to help us out,

03:29.460 --> 03:30.540
We got a game.

03:30.540 --> 03:32.550
Okay, okay.
Will you excuse me, baby?

03:32.550 --> 03:34.050
Ooh! Anything

03:34.050 --> 03:35.420
you say, sugar lips.

03:35.670 --> 03:37.050
Boys.

03:37.250 --> 03:39.300
Sugar lips, huh?

03:39.720 --> 03:41.300
How about that Sheila?

03:41.300 --> 03:44.720
There's one manicurist
who can curl your cuticles!

03:45.010 --> 03:46.980
We're talking about
hockey, not cuticles.

03:47.260 --> 03:49.350
Gentlemen, I have a business
to run here.

03:49.760 --> 03:51.680
Yeah, but... but
you're our goalie.

03:51.980 --> 03:53.070
Without you,
what chance do we have

03:53.070 --> 03:54.850
against
the Shotz Hot Shots?

03:55.070 --> 03:56.650
Very little.

03:56.650 --> 03:58.150
What's with you, Malph?

03:58.150 --> 03:59.660
Ever since you took
over this football pool,

03:59.660 --> 04:00.940
we haven't been able
to talk to you.

04:01.190 --> 04:02.280
You can still
talk to me.

04:02.780 --> 04:03.780
The only difference
is now it costs money.

04:04.280 --> 04:05.110
All right,

04:05.360 --> 04:06.950
any three teams to win,

04:06.950 --> 04:08.280
college or pro,
dollar minimum,

04:08.500 --> 04:10.080
dollar gets you ten.
Forget it.

04:10.580 --> 04:11.580
Like my rings, guys?

04:11.580 --> 04:13.090
Wait a minute.
You're giving ten to one?

04:13.090 --> 04:14.090
Uh-huh.

04:14.090 --> 04:15.590
All right, I'll
take one of those.

04:15.590 --> 04:16.420
Here you go.

04:16.670 --> 04:18.260
Rich, I'll
need a dollar.

04:18.260 --> 04:19.760
I'm good for it.

04:19.760 --> 04:21.760
Oh, yeah.
You're my friend.

04:23.600 --> 04:25.680
Okay, I'll give
you till tonight.

04:25.680 --> 04:27.680
Malph, are you
playing hockey or not?

04:27.680 --> 04:30.190
One second, Pots.

04:30.190 --> 04:31.640
Wake Forest?

04:32.020 --> 04:34.110
You're picking Wake Forest
to beat Notre Dame?

04:34.110 --> 04:36.640
(stifling laughter)

04:36.890 --> 04:37.980
I like the points.

04:37.980 --> 04:40.400
Some guys will do anything
to throw away their money.

04:40.730 --> 04:42.320
See you, Pots.

04:42.320 --> 04:44.820
Keep going for those
long shots, Richie.

04:44.820 --> 04:48.320
Okay, okay, one hour
till game time!

04:48.320 --> 04:49.820
Put down your bets.

04:49.820 --> 04:51.320
Bruiser!

04:51.320 --> 04:53.240
Take a card.

04:53.630 --> 04:56.210
He's even taking
a bet from Bruiser.

04:56.210 --> 04:57.130
He's sick.

04:57.410 --> 04:59.500
Oh, yeah,
but he's rich.

04:59.500 --> 05:01.000
Hey, sugar lips!

05:01.000 --> 05:01.880
Hey, baby.

05:02.220 --> 05:03.300
Girls!

05:03.300 --> 05:05.310
Hey. Fonz,
Fonz, Fonz.

05:06.310 --> 05:08.310
Wait a minute,
wait a minute,
wait a minute.

05:08.310 --> 05:09.730
I said girls,
not candy canes.

05:11.140 --> 05:12.980
Yeah, but we got to talk
to you about something.

05:13.230 --> 05:14.180
Yeah? What about?

05:14.480 --> 05:15.520
We haven't got a goalie, Fonz.

05:15.900 --> 05:16.480
What happened to Ralph?

05:16.850 --> 05:18.940
Well, he... he's
gotten carried away

05:18.940 --> 05:20.940
with these football
betting cards.

05:20.940 --> 05:21.940
Yeah, I noticed.
I noticed.

05:21.940 --> 05:23.940
He's a big boy.
It's his funeral.

05:23.940 --> 05:26.330
Hey, Fonz, you want
to be our goalie?

05:26.580 --> 05:28.910
You want to be a puck?

05:30.700 --> 05:33.200
No, thanks.

05:33.200 --> 05:34.000
Come on, Pots.

05:34.200 --> 05:35.280
Yeah.
Thanks anyway, Fonz.

05:35.280 --> 05:36.290
Yeah, Fonz.

05:38.290 --> 05:39.790
All right, now,
girls, let's get
down to business.

05:39.790 --> 05:41.290
Let's get down
to business.

05:41.290 --> 05:43.090
Whoever catches
this comb,

05:43.290 --> 05:44.260
gets to drive me home, huh?

05:45.760 --> 05:48.630
Ooh, you lucky girls.
Here you go.

05:48.850 --> 05:50.270
All right,
all right!

05:50.550 --> 05:51.630
Congratulations,
Cicely.

05:51.630 --> 05:53.020
Now go out there
and warm up the car.

05:55.360 --> 05:56.440
Oh, you know,
I'll tell you something.

05:56.440 --> 05:57.940
My heart is
like Mount Rushmore.

05:57.940 --> 05:59.440
I understand it's cold.

05:59.440 --> 06:01.280
I understand it's cold, all
right? You can all ride along.

06:01.480 --> 06:02.560
(gasping)
That's right.

06:02.560 --> 06:05.650
Those of you
that don't fit,
run along the sides.

06:05.650 --> 06:11.650
♪ La, la-la, la,
la, la-la, la... la ♪

06:11.650 --> 06:14.620
♪ La, la-la, la, la, la-la, la ♪

06:14.620 --> 06:17.460
♪ La-la-la-la-la-la-la. ♪

06:17.960 --> 06:21.410
Oh, Mom, why did you have
to get succotash again?

06:21.800 --> 06:23.880
That's your
father's favorite,

06:23.880 --> 06:25.890
and besides,
it's very healthy for you.

06:26.300 --> 06:28.760
Well, it may be healthy,
but it makes me sick.

06:29.010 --> 06:30.590
Will you just
put away the groceries?

06:30.590 --> 06:32.590
Your father will be home
from his Leopard meeting,

06:32.590 --> 06:33.930
and he'll be hungry
as a bear.

06:34.310 --> 06:35.680
Oh, good one, Mom.

06:35.900 --> 06:37.480
What? What did I say?

06:37.480 --> 06:38.820
You know--
leopard, bear.
What?

06:39.100 --> 06:41.680
Forget it.

06:41.680 --> 06:44.190
Look, Rich, if you could
just give me the dollar.

06:44.190 --> 06:46.610
Oh, Ralph, don't
you look spiffy?

06:46.940 --> 06:48.910
Thank you. Thank you.

06:49.160 --> 06:50.740
So, how are things
on the riverboat?

06:51.110 --> 06:52.660
Sit on it.

06:54.500 --> 06:55.530
How was the hockey game?

06:55.920 --> 06:57.200
We lost, 12 to nothing.

06:57.450 --> 06:59.450
Oh. Is that bad?

06:59.790 --> 07:04.260
Not when you consider we had
a German Shepherd for a goalie.

07:04.540 --> 07:07.130
Hey, Rich, wait a minute.

07:07.130 --> 07:08.590
Where are you going?

07:08.590 --> 07:09.630
I'm going upstairs
to change my clothes.

07:09.630 --> 07:11.100
Why? Do you want
to make a bet

07:11.100 --> 07:13.130
on what color
socks I put on?

07:13.130 --> 07:14.100
Aw, come on Rich.

07:14.100 --> 07:15.130
Football's my specialty.

07:15.130 --> 07:16.640
Pick a pro team.

07:16.640 --> 07:18.140
No. No, I lost a dollar
today, and that's it.

07:18.140 --> 07:18.940
I'm not betting anymore.

07:19.110 --> 07:20.690
Oh, Rich,
what's a buck

07:20.690 --> 07:22.190
to an ambitious
kid like you?

07:22.190 --> 07:23.980
Green Bay Packers
are a cinch to win.

07:24.140 --> 07:25.230
Don't hand me that.

07:25.230 --> 07:27.030
Everybody knows
Paul Hornung's got a bad leg.

07:27.230 --> 07:28.820
He'll play
in a wheelchair.

07:28.820 --> 07:30.320
What's the difference?

07:30.320 --> 07:32.290
Everybody in Milwaukee
bets Green Bay.

07:32.620 --> 07:33.570
That could be
a pretty good game.

07:33.870 --> 07:35.400
A great game.
Here. Green Bay's
the third one down.

07:35.790 --> 07:37.370
I see it.
I see Green Bay.

07:37.370 --> 07:40.380
What does your dad
think of this?

07:40.380 --> 07:41.380
Are you kidding?

07:41.380 --> 07:42.880
He doesn't know.

07:42.880 --> 07:45.160
He'd crack up.
He'd go ding-dong.

07:45.410 --> 07:47.500
I think you're getting a little
carried away here, Ralph.

07:47.500 --> 07:49.800
I mean, at ten to one,
what happens if you lose?

07:49.970 --> 07:52.050
The odds never go
against the house.

07:52.050 --> 07:54.010
Okay, house,
here's your card.

07:54.010 --> 07:55.060
Thanks.

07:55.560 --> 07:57.060
I liked it better when
you were a comic, Ralph.

08:00.560 --> 08:03.070
Why are you following
me up to my room?

08:03.070 --> 08:05.070
Hey, a buck's a buck.

08:05.070 --> 08:07.940
Hey, Rich, you think
Rockefeller got rich
trusting people?

08:08.190 --> 08:11.770
It's always a pleasure
to drive you home, Howie.

08:11.770 --> 08:13.280
You're such a sweet guy.

08:13.280 --> 08:15.280
Mickey, you don't have
to butter me up.

08:15.280 --> 08:16.780
If the lodge thinks
that Ralph should

08:16.780 --> 08:18.780
be Junior Leopard
of the Year, then he will.

08:19.200 --> 08:20.780
Hello, Howard.

08:20.780 --> 08:21.780
Oh, hi, sweetheart.

08:21.780 --> 08:23.700
Did you get
the succotash?
Oh.

08:24.000 --> 08:25.090
Hello, Mickey,

08:25.090 --> 08:27.040
Ralph is
right upstairs.

08:27.040 --> 08:28.590
Oh, good.
We can drive home together.

08:28.590 --> 08:29.590
We'll have some laughs.

08:29.590 --> 08:31.010
The kid's got
a great personality.

08:31.340 --> 08:32.380
Right, Howie?

08:32.760 --> 08:35.850
I wish you'd please
stop calling me Howie.

08:35.850 --> 08:37.850
Oh, Howie, the
kid's a natural.

08:37.850 --> 08:39.640
He's cute and witty.

08:39.850 --> 08:40.940
You know, when
they made Ralph,

08:40.940 --> 08:41.940
they broke the mold.

08:42.360 --> 08:44.860
I can see why.

08:45.190 --> 08:47.780
Do you have
a teenage daughter, Mickey?

08:47.780 --> 08:49.780
No.
Would you like one?

08:50.200 --> 08:53.650
(laughing)
Good one, Howie.

08:53.900 --> 08:55.480
RALPH:
So, Rich, look.

08:55.900 --> 08:57.490
I took the odds
from all the papers,

08:57.490 --> 08:59.490
and then I figured out
the averages.

08:59.490 --> 09:02.490
Oh, hi, Dad.
I was just explaining averages,

09:02.490 --> 09:03.960
helping Richie with some math.

09:03.960 --> 09:06.500
Oh, what
a kid, huh?

09:06.500 --> 09:08.380
Helps his friends, huh?

09:08.660 --> 09:10.170
Hey, my boy, Ralphie.
Right, Pop. Right.

09:10.500 --> 09:11.920
Well, we better

09:12.130 --> 09:13.220
hit the road, Ralphie.

09:13.220 --> 09:14.220
Okay, Dad.

09:14.220 --> 09:15.720
Uh! Let's give them one.

09:16.220 --> 09:17.220
Okay, Dad.

09:17.640 --> 09:19.680
Hey, Dad,

09:20.060 --> 09:21.140
you know, I just came
back from Africa,

09:21.140 --> 09:23.150
and I played cards
with the natives.

09:23.150 --> 09:24.650
Zulus?

09:24.650 --> 09:25.650
No. I won.

09:25.650 --> 09:26.980
Ha-cha-cha!
Ha-cha-cha!

09:33.520 --> 09:35.110
Come and get it.

09:35.110 --> 09:40.110
Well, thank goodness we still
have Abbott and Costello.

09:40.530 --> 09:43.580
Oh, good!
I'm hungry as a bear.

09:43.580 --> 09:45.250
(dog barking)

09:45.750 --> 09:49.210
Oh, Mom, uh, could you save
the bone for our goalie?

09:49.590 --> 09:51.620
Yes, dear.

09:54.540 --> 09:56.960
You have a dog for a goalie?

09:57.350 --> 09:59.720
Yeah. He played today.

10:01.970 --> 10:06.390
♪ Wa, wa, wa-wa, wa-wa, wa ♪

10:06.390 --> 10:09.280
♪ Wa-wa, wa-wa, wa. ♪

10:09.560 --> 10:12.140
RICHIE:
Can't you fix the color, Al?

10:12.140 --> 10:14.150
AL:
What do you want from me?
I can't.

10:14.150 --> 10:17.120
Bruiser broke the antenna off.

10:19.400 --> 10:20.990
Such a boring game.

10:20.990 --> 10:22.740
He dropped it
again. Look.

10:28.040 --> 10:30.050
Aw, come on.

10:30.050 --> 10:33.000
Gentlemen, gentlemen.

10:35.550 --> 10:36.970
Green Bay's down by 11 points.

10:37.220 --> 10:39.310
They'll catch up.
You know the Packers.

10:39.310 --> 10:41.260
(softly):
They haven't got a prayer.

10:41.260 --> 10:42.810
There's two
minutes to go.

10:42.810 --> 10:45.230
Let's have a soda,
you beautiful thing.

10:45.560 --> 10:46.560
Come on.
Put in Hornung!

10:46.900 --> 10:48.480
Don't worry, Pots.
They'll put him in.

10:48.480 --> 10:49.980
(softly):
They'll never put him in.

10:49.980 --> 10:51.980
The man should be
in a wheelchair.

10:51.980 --> 10:54.770
Okay, service! May we
have service, Alfred?

10:55.020 --> 10:58.610
Ralph, I'm trying
to watch a football game.

10:58.610 --> 11:01.110
Al, I'm buying sodas
for the house.

11:01.610 --> 11:03.410
Oh. Well, I can
read about it
in the newspaper.

11:03.580 --> 11:05.000
Could you turn up
the sound?

11:05.250 --> 11:06.830
There isn't any sound.

11:06.830 --> 11:09.250
After the Wake Forest game,
Bruiser bit off the knob.

11:11.420 --> 11:12.920
(laughing)

11:14.870 --> 11:16.710
Look at that. Come on!

11:17.090 --> 11:18.960
Come on!

11:19.180 --> 11:22.260
MAN: We're gonna
lose our shirts.

11:22.260 --> 11:24.270
Hi, Fonz.

11:24.270 --> 11:25.770
I'm buying
everybody sodas,

11:25.770 --> 11:27.270
but I want you to
have a cheeseburger.

11:27.270 --> 11:28.550
How does that sound?

11:28.800 --> 11:30.390
Let me tell
you something, Malph.

11:30.390 --> 11:31.890
I got my own problems,
all right?

11:31.890 --> 11:33.810
I got to find a piston,
and they ain't cheap.

11:34.190 --> 11:36.700
You need money,
and I can use an associate.

11:37.030 --> 11:38.610
Hey! Hey!
All right! Yeah!

11:39.120 --> 11:39.620
Interception!

11:39.620 --> 11:42.070
Green Bay just
intercepted a pass!

11:42.450 --> 11:43.490
POTSIE:
They're going all the way
for the touchdown!

11:43.870 --> 11:45.740
(all cheering)

11:45.960 --> 11:48.540
I told you guys
they'd catch up.

11:48.540 --> 11:49.540
Thank you, my dear.

11:52.160 --> 11:53.710
(all cheering)

11:54.080 --> 11:57.170
I could use a tough cookie
like you to help me collect.

11:59.670 --> 12:04.170
First of all,
the Fonz is not a cookie.

12:04.170 --> 12:07.180
See, a cookie is something
you put in your mouth.

12:07.180 --> 12:09.680
Like this.

12:09.680 --> 12:11.680
Bad choice of words.

12:11.680 --> 12:13.680
Let... let me rephrase.

12:13.680 --> 12:16.190
Yeah, do that. Rephrase.

12:18.690 --> 12:20.070
Fonzie,

12:20.360 --> 12:23.240
I am prepared to offer you
ten percent of my business.

12:23.410 --> 12:25.490
Malph, do you have any idea

12:25.490 --> 12:26.950
what a dirty business
you're getting into?

12:28.780 --> 12:30.370
